Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following three stories:

  • I Led Earth's Strangest Safari!
  • The Cave Creatures of Xota!
  • I Was a Prisoner of the Rainbow People!

It also contains the following comic strip:

  • Professor Eureka

I Led Earth's Strangest Safari

A safari guide is having a rather average day, that is up until he's greeted by a trio of aliens from Neptune who wish to partake in a safari; however, things aren't as simple as they seem when an elephant they find holds the key to Neptune's fate.

The Cave Creatures of Xota

Two explorers wind up lost in a strange cave system, while inside they find a strange new civilization of giant amphibious creatures. Unfortunately the creatures wind up being hostile and the explorers end up in the fight of their lives!

I Was a Prisoner of the Rainbow People

Somewhere over the rainbow lies a mysterious new world which is home of the Rainbow People. When Mark Winters finds himself there he ends up a captive of their queen, Queen Brilliance. If he's to escape he must help the Queen and her people defeat the notorious Marston gang!

Professor Eureka

Professor Eureka creates a brand new hair grow solution, but does it work as expected?
name: I Led Earth's Strangest Safari! / The Cave Creatures of Xota! / I Was a Prisoner of the Rainbow People

volume.name: The New Adventures of Charlie Chan

description:
Secret of the Eternal City!

On the Peruvian Plateau of the Andes Mountains, archaeologist Adam Strange discovers the lost Inca city of Caramanga. Finding a treasure of gold, Adam is assaulted by natives determined to not let his discovery reach the outside world. With no place left to run, Adam jumps off a cliff, but instead of plunging to his death, he finds himself teleported to a jungle with creatures not native to Earth.

A flying ship saves him from one of these creatures, and a beautiful woman comes out. She speaks a language Adam does not recognize, yet Adam makes out that her name is Alanna, and she wishes to bring him to a place called Ranagar. Alanna brings him onboard her flying ship, and shows him the wonders of this new planet. Alanna brings him to a small laboratory, where a balding scientist attaches a headband to him. The headband, a menticizer, instantly teaches Adam their language.

Adam finds out he is on the planet Rann, orbiting the star Alpha Centauri, in the lab of Sardath, Alannas father. Four years ago, Rann transmitted a Zeta Beam to Earth to communicate. Evidently, the beam now serves as a teleportation conduit between Earth and Rann. However, due to the rotation of both planets, the beam intersects at different locations at different windows. Alanna offers to take Adam on a tour of Rann.

While visiting the coastal city of Kamorak, Rann is assaulted by spaceships. Heading back to Sardaths lab, Adam and Alanna find out that the attacking aliens are called the Eternals. They come seeking Vitatron, a rare element. The only place to find Vitatron on Rann is in Samakand, the city that only appears every 25 years. Samakand reappears from the fourth dimension, just as the Eternals attack. Adam Strange, in a commandeered spaceship, stalls the Eternals. The Eternals finally land in Samakand, just as it disappears again. The Eternals are trapped. However, just as Alanna and Adam celebrate, Adam fades as the Zeta Beam wears off, returning him to Earth. Adam vows to go to the next Zeta Beam location in 62 days and return to Rann.

The Planet and the Pendulum!

Adam Strange has traveled to the coast of Singapore, where he awaits the next Zeta Beam to Rann. The beam strikes him, bringing him to a Rann he does not recognize. Instead of advanced technology, he finds a barbaric race. Two bystanders call him a sorcerer from Ranagar, and capture him. They bring Adam to Chief Zoora, leader of the ruined city of Yardana. Zoora places Adam in the Rainbow Doom, which teleports him someplace else.

Finding a wrecked spaceship, Adam also discovers Sardath and Alanna. They are on Anthorann, a neighboring planet of Rann. When the Samakand joined Rann society, they brought new technology that Rann brought to the primitive tribes. However, the tribes saw the other Rannians as sorcerers and banished them to Anthorann. Adam contacts Ranns city of New Ranagar on Anthorann, and asks for a pickup.

A New Ranagar patrol comes, but warns them to hurry, because Anthorann is under attack by the alien Morleen. The Morleen plan on using a large pendulum blade to slice through the domed city of New Ranagar. Adam destroys the fulcrum of the pendulum, saving New Ranagar. However, just as he finishes, the Zeta Beam wears off, returning him to Earth.

Vignettes:

  • Look to the Stars!
  • Our Strange Universe!
  • Curious Comets
  • The Three-in-One Star
name: Secret of the Eternal City / The Planet and the Pendulum

We Battled the Sand Creature

The man named Zaccine is a world class sand artist, manipulating it with his hands to create fantastical designs. When Zaccine creates his newest design, a dinosaur, it comes to life and begins terrorizing the beach!

I Fought the Cloud Menace

Bud Atkins and Rick are two freelance prospectors flying over a remote location in South America when they come across something strange, a cloud menace surrounding the small village of Duida. Can they stop it in time or is it lights out for Duida?

I Was King of the Mechanical Men

A man comes across a strange trio of giant robots named the mechanical men. He learns he can control them and uses them to commit great deeds of heroism; however, they soon stop obeying his orders and create havoc around the globe!

Professor Eureka

Professor Eureka takes a trip to Egypt!

Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following three stories:

  • I Was Earth's First Exile!
  • We Hunted the Forbidden Treasure!
  • We Were 20th Century Cavemen!

It also contains the following comic strip:

  • Peter Puptent

I Was Earth's First Exile

Captain Ferguson is on an exploration in space when he finds himself bathed in cosmic rays. Unable to return to Earth due to the large amounts of radiation on his body he lands on a strange planet of which had never been seen before. It's on this planet that he learns the radiation has given him strange new powers!

We Hunted the Forbidden Treasure

Treasure Hunts Incorporated is a business designed purely for the act of locating and obtaining lost treasures. After the group learns of a mysterious Aztec treasure they begin searching; however, is it true that the treasure is cursed or is that some sort of local rumor?

We Were 20th Century Cavemen

When a trio of scientists create a device known as the Rejuva-Ray in an attempt to obtain eternal youth; however, the device malfunctions and brings everything on an exotic island back to life, including the fossils hidden underground! Now they must fight against strange beasts and dinosaurs in an attempt to survive!
name: We Were 20th Century Cavemen
